# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Trace Mate — environment variables (TEMPLATE — committed to git)
#
# How to use:
#   1. Copy this file to .env.local              (frontend, gitignored)
#   2. Copy/edit scripts/setup-supabase-secrets.sh (backend, gitignored)
#   3. Fill real values into .env.local + the script — NOT into this file
#
# ⚠️  DO NOT put real secret values in this file. It is committed to git.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── FRONTEND (.env.local + Cloudflare Pages → Env Vars) ──────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your Supabase "anon public" key>

# Admin gating no longer reads frontend env vars — UI gating is driven by
# `profiles.is_admin`. Grant via:
#   select public.set_admin_by_email('you@example.com', true);


# ─── BACKEND (Supabase Edge Function secrets) ──────────────────
# Set these via:  bash scripts/setup-supabase-secrets.sh
#
# DODO_API_KEY=dodo_test_<server-side only>
# DODO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_<from Webhooks page>
# DODO_ENVIRONMENT=test_mode
#
# Product IDs (not secrets — public references in your Dodo account):
# DODO_PRODUCT_MONTHLY=pdt_<id>
# DODO_PRODUCT_QUARTERLY=pdt_<id>
# DODO_PRODUCT_LIFETIME=pdt_<id>
#
# Expected per-plan prices in cents (used by dodo-webhook to validate the
# amount on each event). If the webhook sees an amount lower than this for
# the matching plan, it refuses to grant entitlement. Match what's set in Dodo.
# DODO_PRICE_MONTHLY_CENTS=500
# DODO_PRICE_QUARTERLY_CENTS=1000
# DODO_PRICE_LIFETIME_CENTS=1500
# DODO_EXPECTED_CURRENCY=USD
#
# APP_URL=http://localhost:5173                    # in prod: https://yourdomain.com
